## Monorepo Best Practices

### 1. Dependencies

- Use `pnpm` for package management
- Keep dependencies updated
- Use exact versions for critical dependencies
- Separate development and production dependencies

### 2. File Structure

- Maintain consistency in directory structure
- Use uniform naming conventions
- Separate source code from configuration files

### 3. Build and Deploy

- Incremental build for development
- Complete build for production
- Bundle size analysis
- Asset optimization

### 4. Testing

- Unit tests per package
- Integration tests at monorepo level
- Consolidated coverage reports
- Accessibility testing

## Monorepo Checklist

- [ ] Consistent directory structure
